<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-706-204  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 706 204.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>UNIX World  Oct 1989 v6 n10 pS61(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>No safe bets on network management. (integrating networkmanagement tools)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Baldwin, Howard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Integrating complex networks and network-management tools isalways difficult and can become a form of crisis management in theevent of technical difficulties.andP;  Performance analysis and faultisolation are the two key aspects of network management, and bothencompass all of the first four layers of the seven-layer OSImodel.andP;  The introduction of architectures for network managementindicates its growing importance.andP;  ATandamp;T's United NetworkManagement Architecture is a cornerstone whose counterparts arenot yet fully developed.andP;  UNIX is widely considered an idealnetwork-management platform, with several Unix-based T1 networkmanagement products now in the marketplace.andP;  Managers should makesure to have the right response before entering the field andshould be aware of what questions to ask before attempting todevelop a network solution.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Network ManagementComputer Systems IntegrationLocal Area NetworksConnectivityNetwork Management SoftwareMultivendor Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>